\newlabel{tutorial:id10}{{2.1.4}{26}{Considering the given performance tableau, the {\hyperref [\detokenize {techDoc:outrankingDigraphs.BipolarOutrankingDigraph}]{\sphinxcrossref {\sphinxcode {outrankingDigraphs.BipolarOutrankingDigraph}}}} class constructor computes the characteristic value \(r(x\,S\,y)\) of a pairwise outranking relation “\(x\,S\,y\)” (see \phantomsection {\hyperref [\detokenize {tutorial:bis-2013}]{\sphinxcrossref {{[}BIS-2013{]}}}}, \phantomsection {\hyperref [\detokenize {tutorial:adt-l7}]{\sphinxcrossref {{[}ADT-L7{]}}}}) in a default valuation domain {[}-100.0,+100.0{]} with the median value 0.0 acting as indeterminate characteristic value. The semantics of r(x S y) are the following:}{section*.67}{}}
\newlabel{tutorial:id11}{{2.1.4}{26}{Considering the given performance tableau, the {\hyperref [\detokenize {techDoc:outrankingDigraphs.BipolarOutrankingDigraph}]{\sphinxcrossref {\sphinxcode {outrankingDigraphs.BipolarOutrankingDigraph}}}} class constructor computes the characteristic value \(r(x\,S\,y)\) of a pairwise outranking relation “\(x\,S\,y\)” (see \phantomsection {\hyperref [\detokenize {tutorial:bis-2013}]{\sphinxcrossref {{[}BIS-2013{]}}}}, \phantomsection {\hyperref [\detokenize {tutorial:adt-l7}]{\sphinxcrossref {{[}ADT-L7{]}}}}) in a default valuation domain {[}-100.0,+100.0{]} with the median value 0.0 acting as indeterminate characteristic value. The semantics of r(x S y) are the following:}{section*.68}{}}
